messages.message: i think this can be a good q1 item for the frontend team -- in Build, clicking on different buttons very quickly without waiting for them to finish loading sometimes triggers weird edge cases for me that goes away after refresh / triggering things again.
with the ocr issue, ask them to turn on object detection -- that forces ocr every page. likely this pdf has a text layer that doesn't include everything

@Bastiane can you give me and Serena access to this project? I suspect the inconsistency is a mixture of frontend issues and model changes. When I upload the same file twice to a project I created, I only see very slight model changes (an addition of a `-` or `%`), so I don't think the inconsistency is completely due to model variability
Need to get admin access for that. In the meantime, feel free to use my account.
are your login credentials shared somewhere?

I can confirm that object detection has been on. Also even between each time I logged in, I can see different results. Take the field Distributions as an example, it returned no value found yesterday and 33,687 this morning.

btw it is expected to see different results if “No value found” is shown for a field

when you reload a project, if a field has “No value found”, we will rerun that field to retry extraction, so it’s possible a field changes from “No value found” to “33.687", for example

what’s unexpected is for a field to have a value and then become “No value found” (ie as shown in the customer-provided screenshots (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C0516UPPMT3/p1705622512886139?thread_ts=1705615761.747949&cid=C0516UPPMT3))

if a field has a value, and that value is saved, we will not rerun extraction for that field
oh i interpreted the two screenshots to be two different projects, not the same project at different times
yeah, since the screenshots only include the right part of the page, it’s hard to tell
I forwarded you the email, and here's the full context
it says inconsistency between two accounts

are we sure that the digitization settings are the same in both projects?

i see some discrepancies in punctuation characters (currency symbols, parentheses, negative signs, etc), which seems to imply discrepancies in the underlying OCR text
that's possible, but we also reproduced that adding more fields can cause "No value found" to be returned for "Distributions"

so i feel like the more likely scenario is, in the first account, they added the fields one-at-a-time, which works. then in the commercial account, they added all the fields at once, and somehow that causes "No value found" to be returned for "Distributions"
